WHO   — SEGA DREAMCAST — an exereunesis sphere — the teardown
WHAT  — Sega's final console arrived early and forward-looking: a fast Hitachi SH-4 CPU, a PowerVR graphics chip, a built-in modem for online play, and a memory card with its own screen. Brilliant and beloved, it was undone by the PS2's hype and Sega's finances.
WHERE — the teardown — a made machine, opened and explored  Framework inputs: the chips; the buses; the spec; the lore  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
